.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_SharedMethods
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Shared Methods script is a collection of reusable static methods that are used across a range of different scripts.

methods.name: FindEvenInactiveComponent<T>()
methods.summary: Finds the first component of a given type.
methods.remarks: This method returns components from active as well as inactive s in the scene. It doesn't return assets. For performance reasons it is recommended to not use this function every frame. Cache the result in a member variable at startup instead.
methods.returns: The found component. If no component is found is returned.

params.value: The component type to search for. Must be a subclass of .

methods.syntax: public static T FindEvenInactiveComponent<T>()
methods.linkedSyntax: public static T FindEvenInactiveComponent<T>()

methods.name: FindEvenInactiveComponents<T>()
methods.summary: Finds all components of a given type.
methods.remarks: This method returns components from active as well as inactive s in the scene. It doesn't return assets. For performance reasons it is recommended to not use this function every frame. Cache the result in a member variable at startup instead.
methods.returns: All the found components. If no component is found an empty array is returned.

params.value: The component type to search for. Must be a subclass of .

methods.syntax: public static T[] FindEvenInactiveComponents<T>()
methods.linkedSyntax: public static T[] FindEvenInactiveComponents<T>()

methods.name: FindEvenInactiveGameObject<T>(string gameObjectName)
methods.summary: Finds the first with a given name and an ancestor that has a specific component.
methods.remarks: This method returns active as well as inactive s in the scene. It doesn't return assets. For performance reasons it is recommended to not use this function every frame. Cache the result in a member variable at startup instead.
methods.returns: The with name gameObjectName and an ancestor that has a T. If no such is found is returned.

params.value: The name of the wanted . If it contains a '/' character, this method traverses the hierarchy like a path name, beginning on the game object that has a component of type T.
The component type that needs to be on an ancestor of the wanted . Must be a subclass of .

methods.syntax: public static GameObject FindEvenInactiveGameObject<T>(string gameObjectName)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static GameObject FindEvenInactiveGameObject<T>(string gameObjectName)
